    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>An estoc is a sword about as long as a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/equipment/weapons/weapon-descriptions/sword-bastard\">bastard sword</a>, but designed exclusively for thrusting attacks. Its “blade” is a steel spike with a triangular, square, or hexagonal cross-section.</em></p>\n<p>Like the bastard sword, an estoc requires special training to use it one handed, but it can also be wielded as a two-handed martial weapon.</p>\n<p>When you wield an estoc with one hand, treat it as a one-handed weapon; when you wield an estoc with two hands, treat it as a two-handed weapon. If you can use the estoc proficiently with one hand, you can also use the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/feats/combat-feats/weapon-finesse-combat\">Weapon Finesse</a>&nbsp;feat to apply your&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Dexterity-Dex-\">Dexterity</a>&nbsp;modifier instead of your&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Strength-Str-\">Strength</a>&nbsp;modifier on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Attack-Roll\">attack rolls</a>&nbsp;when wielding an estoc sized for you with one or two hands, even though it isn’t a light weapon.</p>",
